I love you, too, Lou.

30:25.658 --> 30:27.618
[ Engine starts]

30:39.380 --> 30:41.007
[Whirring]

30:44.427 --> 30:46.763
[ <i>"Deck the Ha//s" plays</i> ]

30:47.680 --> 30:51.142
Peppermint twist for me and a
whiskey for Abe, both on my tab.

30:54.354 --> 30:56.147
Charlie.

30:56.272 --> 30:59.400
Charlie Manx.

31:01.069 --> 31:03.321
Hey, feeling lucky tonight?

31:06.115 --> 31:07.784
Let's have a throw.

31:08.826 --> 31:11.329
Not tonight
and never with you, Snake.

31:11.454 --> 31:16.292
Mother Manx,
rest her whore soul,

31:16.417 --> 31:19.003
didn't raise any fools.

31:21.297 --> 31:24.258
[Chuckles lightly]

31:29.472 --> 31:31.307
CHARLIE:
Cheers, Abe.

31:31.432 --> 31:33.267
I bought the house a drink
in your honor

31:33.393 --> 31:35.269
when I heard you were dead.

31:35.395 --> 31:37.188
Mm.

31:37.313 --> 31:38.981
I'm touched.

31:41.567 --> 31:44.487
You were relieved to hear
of my passing, no doubt,

31:44.612 --> 31:46.948
thinking you were free and clear
of your debts.

31:47.073 --> 31:48.074
I knew you weren't dead.

31:48.199 --> 31:51.285
And that this drink wasn't free.

31:51.411 --> 31:53.579
The Hourglass.

31:53.704 --> 31:55.206
I want to meet him.

31:55.331 --> 31:58.251
I don't do introductions
anymore.

31:58.376 --> 32:01.754
I've become antisocial
in my retirement.

32:03.172 --> 32:05.883
I remember the days when
the denizens of this world

32:06.008 --> 32:09.262
would run and hide when
they heard old honest Abe

32:09.387 --> 32:12.890
had left his Empty Forest
to travel the Night Road.

32:13.015 --> 32:15.852
Now you're the one
who's running scared.

32:15.977 --> 32:20.189
It's that girl and her bike
who scare you, as they should.

32:20.314 --> 32:22.191
She killed you once.

32:22.316 --> 32:23.693
You don't let this go,

32:23.818 --> 32:25.945
they'll be scraping your body
off the Night Road.

32:26.070 --> 32:29.824
I told you the same thing about
the Walking Backwards Man.

32:29.949 --> 32:30.908
If I hadn't intervened --

32:31.033 --> 32:34.454
I was grateful to you then,
and I am grateful to you now.

32:34.579 --> 32:37.290
[Telephone ringing ]

32:40.918 --> 32:44.964
The time has come for you
to show your gratitude.

32:47.884 --> 32:50.136
I wish you were dead, Chuck.

32:50.261 --> 32:52.638
That's the spirit, Abe.

32:54.640 --> 32:56.851
Tell the Hourglass
I look forward

32:56.976 --> 32:59.520
to making his acquaintance.

32:59.645 --> 33:02.148
Tell my goddaughter I miss her.

33:02.273 --> 33:04.317
[ "O Holy Night" playing ]

33:13.409 --> 33:15.077
<i>MILLIE:
Hello, Father.</i>

33:15.203 --> 33:16.621
Hello, Sugar Plum.

33:16.746 --> 33:18.915
<i>Uncle Abe says Merry Christmas.</i>

33:19.040 --> 33:21.083
MILLIE:
When are you coming back?

33:21.209 --> 33:22.710
<i>CHARLIE: There's been
a <i>slight delay, my joy,</i></i>

33:22.835 --> 33:23.711
<i>but don't you worry.</i>

33:23.836 --> 33:25.713
<i>You'll have</i> a <i>new friend
to play with in no time</i>

33:25.838 --> 33:27.924
<i>and you'll be very glad
you waited.</i>

33:30.968 --> 33:33.679
Assuming you've been a good girl
while I've been away.

33:33.804 --> 33:39.435
I saw a light from a house
on top of Candy Mountain.

33:39.560 --> 33:41.812
You know that children
who venture beyond the gates

33:41.938 --> 33:43.356
wind up on the naughty list.

33:43.481 --> 33:44.899
Who's up there?

33:45.024 --> 33:46.400
<i>CHARLIE:
Nothing's up there.</i>

33:46.526 --> 33:50.238
Have you been naughty,
Millicent?

33:50.363 --> 33:52.114
No, Father.

33:52.240 --> 33:54.784
<i>CHARLIE: Fibbing will get you on
the naughty list all the same.</i>

33:54.909 --> 33:58.746
I depend on you to spread
Christmas cheer while I'm away.

34:01.082 --> 34:02.667
Take care of the children.

34:02.792 --> 34:04.085
I know.

34:05.294 --> 34:07.380
Merry Christmas, Father.

34:08.965 --> 34:12.510
Merry Christmas, my child.

34:13.719 --> 34:18.558
<i>J'</i> O <i>night J'</i>

34:18.683 --> 34:23.771
<i>J'</i> O <i>night divine J'</i>

34:23.896 --> 34:26.899
[ Static buzzing ]

34:34.739 --> 34:36.324
[Engine shuts off]

35:02.977 --> 35:05.813
You're a little late
for your rescue mission.

35:07.231 --> 35:10.067
You gonna kill me
with your gas can?

35:10.192 --> 35:11.944
Worked pretty well last time.

35:12.069 --> 35:13.571
I'll admit I underestimated you.

35:13.696 --> 35:16.073
I promise I won't
make that mistake again.

35:19.452 --> 35:22.622
I think, perhaps, this time,
you underestimated me.

35:23.956 --> 35:27.209
Do you know where we are,
Victoria McQueen?

35:27.960 --> 35:29.128
[Thunder crashes]

35:29.253 --> 35:30.504
VIC:
No, but it doesn't matter.

35:33.341 --> 35:35.968
We're on the Night Road,

35:36.093 --> 35:38.220
an lnscape formed by
the collective unconscious

35:38.346 --> 35:41.557
of a community of people
just like us.

35:43.059 --> 35:47.605
Access requires a certain
darkness of the soul.

35:47.730 --> 35:51.692
What darkness has been lurking
within you since last we meet?

35:51.817 --> 35:55.655
Teen pregnancy?
Child born out of wedlock?

35:55.780 --> 35:59.367
His father burned to death
along with the innocent Bradley

35:59.492 --> 36:02.161
all as a consequence
of your sins,

36:02.286 --> 36:08.084
lust, anger, pride, abandonment.

36:08.209 --> 36:09.877
None of that matters, Charlie.

36:10.002 --> 36:12.546
What matters is
you can't have Wayne.

36:12.672 --> 36:14.131
I will stop you
even if it kills me.

36:14.256 --> 36:15.549
That's a promise.

36:15.675 --> 36:17.134
CHARLIE:
More like a wish, I think.

36:17.259 --> 36:19.512
To die by my hand
so you don't have to face

36:19.637 --> 36:21.931
your family or your failures
ever again.

36:22.056 --> 36:24.141
A mercy I'm more than willing
to provide.

36:25.851 --> 36:27.728
And Wayne?
In Christmasland,

36:27.853 --> 36:31.190
he'll forget all about
his drunk, whore mother.

36:31.315 --> 36:32.566
Another mercy.

36:32.692 --> 36:35.361
It appears I'm the best thing to
ever happen to you, Vic McQueen.

36:35.486 --> 36:38.948
And I'll be the best thing
to ever happen to Wayne.

36:39.073 --> 36:40.783
[ Engine starts]

36:43.411 --> 36:45.204
[ Engine starts]

36:45.329 --> 36:46.414
[ Lighter clicks]

36:55.965 --> 36:59.093
[Thunder crashing]

37:04.765 --> 37:06.892
[ Brakes squeal]

37:09.437 --> 37:11.439
[ Engine revs]

37:14.191 --> 37:17.069
[Tires squeal ]

37:36.797 --> 37:40.050
[ Insects chirping ]

37:44.096 --> 37:46.056
Oh, Christ.

37:46.182 --> 37:48.058
[Sighs]

37:48.184 --> 37:51.103
[Engine whirring]

37:54.940 --> 37:57.359
Mm.

37:57.485 --> 37:58.778
[Clicks tongue]

38:04.408 --> 38:08.704
Nice. Nice.
Getting drunk, joyriding.

38:08.829 --> 38:11.248
I'm not dr--
l'm -- l'm...l'm fine.

38:11.373 --> 38:14.335
Yeah, you do not look fine.
Come on.

38:22.092 --> 38:24.053
Take these.

38:27.223 --> 38:29.517
- Thanks.
- Mm-hmm.

38:29.642 --> 38:32.436
[GulPS]

38:32.561 --> 38:33.729
[Glass clinks]

38:35.648 --> 38:37.608
You need to
get your shit together,

38:37.733 --> 38:39.443
go back to your kid.

38:44.406 --> 38:45.866
Ma, I...

38:45.991 --> 38:47.701
[ Scoffs 1

38:49.912 --> 38:52.498
I try hard, and I fail.

38:54.333 --> 38:55.751
I make bad decisions.

38:55.876 --> 38:58.003
We all have regrets, Vicki.
It's part of growing up.

39:01.090 --> 39:02.842
Look,LLH

39:02.967 --> 39:04.760
I hurt Wayne
and l-l put him in danger

39:04.885 --> 39:06.220
and then I couldn't protect him.

39:06.345 --> 39:09.390
Mm, I never won a gold medal
for parenting, either.

39:09.515 --> 39:12.560
I think of all the things
I screwed up...

39:12.685 --> 39:14.854
I mean, I never actually
burned down my own house.

39:14.979 --> 39:17.147
Okay. [ Chuckles]

39:20.484 --> 39:23.779
When you are young,
you do not understand

39:23.904 --> 39:25.865
how much a kid is gonna
take from you.

39:28.826 --> 39:32.580
You give him everything you've
got and more than you have.

39:33.455 --> 39:35.082
What if I don't know how to
love him like that?

39:35.207 --> 39:37.001
You don't have to know how,
Vicki.

39:37.126 --> 39:38.878
You just have to stay.

39:39.753 --> 39:41.422
That's what love is.

39:41.547 --> 39:43.215
You stay.

39:43.340 --> 39:46.260
Even though nobody
rewards you for it

39:46.385 --> 39:48.470
and you always feel like
you are screwing up

39:48.596 --> 39:51.223
and a lot of the time, you are.

39:51.348 --> 39:53.392
[Sighs]

39:53.517 --> 39:55.978
A mother stays.

39:56.103 --> 39:58.063
You figure out the rest.

41:09.426 --> 41:11.720
[ Panting ]

41:17.685 --> 41:20.771
[ Door creaks open ]

41:34.868 --> 41:37.121
[Whispering] Millie.

41:44.545 --> 41:46.714
[ Insects chirping ]

42:03.480 --> 42:05.649
[ Knock on door]

42:11.030 --> 42:13.407
Oh, Brat.

42:13.532 --> 42:14.533
You're alive.

42:18.579 --> 42:20.706
- And in one piece.
-[ Chuckles ]

42:22.833 --> 42:24.710
So are you.

42:29.006 --> 42:31.300
I didn't get Manx.
I tried.

42:33.177 --> 42:34.553
It's okay.

42:34.678 --> 42:36.764
He has to get through
all of us.

42:36.889 --> 42:39.892
So we'll stop him this time.
For good.

42:41.518 --> 42:42.519
Okay?

42:43.729 --> 42:45.647
[ D¢or opens]

42:51.570 --> 42:53.489
Thank you.

42:56.825 --> 42:58.452
Hey.
You guys made it.

43:04.958 --> 43:05.959
[ Jacket unzips]

43:06.085 --> 43:08.462
Hey, Bats, are you okay?

43:12.382 --> 43:15.135
I am so sorry
I wasn't there. Hm?

43:15.260 --> 43:16.637
Whatever.

43:16.762 --> 43:18.138
I'm fine.

43:23.143 --> 43:24.561
LOU:
Glad to see you're alright.

43:33.278 --> 43:38.242
You, uh -- You here for a visit
or to stay?

43:40.410 --> 43:41.495
To stay.

43:59.096 --> 44:00.806
[Telephone ringing ]

44:09.857 --> 44:11.358
[Sniffs]

44:11.483 --> 44:12.860
Yes.

44:14.903 --> 44:17.573
Abe, you foul old rummy,

44:17.698 --> 44:21.034
I've told you before I don't
want any more clients from you.

44:23.203 --> 44:24.913
You're joking.

44:27.374 --> 44:30.252
[ Clicks tongue]
Well, in that case,

44:30.377 --> 44:33.255
I would be honored
to meet Charles Manx.

44:37.968 --> 44:40.137
Who is Vic McQueen?
